HEADWORD: Aspersorium
<hw>As`per*so"ri*um</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Aspersoria</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
See <er>Asperse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The stoup, basin, or other
vessel for holy water in Roman Catholic churches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A brush for sprinkling holy water; an
aspergill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

